          {
            "title": "Intro",
            "id": 82512,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Listas ordenadas são úteis quando queremos entender onde pontos de dados individuais, como pontuações, estão em relação aos outros.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"scores = [\" /><text value=\"10\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"11\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"4\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"15\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"11\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"7\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\"]\" /></content></code></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Method call",
            "id": 82513,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Para ordenar uma lista como <code>scores</code>, escrevemos o nome da lista, um ponto <code>.</code>, e então <code>sort()</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"scores = [\" /><text value=\"3\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"6\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"1\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"12\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\"]\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"scores.sort()\" /><text type=\"break\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"23\" endIndex=\"29\" /><option startIndex=\"29\" endIndex=\"30\" /><option startIndex=\"30\" endIndex=\"36\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Certifique-se de escolher <code>scores</code> seguido de <code>.</code> e finalmente <code>sort()</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Display",
            "id": 82517,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Ordenar altera a lista, então quando reutilizamos ou exibimos a lista com <code>print(scores)</code>, ela aparecerá ordenada.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"scores = [\" /><text value=\"3\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"6\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"1\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"12\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\"]\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"scores.sort()\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(scores)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"validatedInput\" isDefault=\"true\" startIndex=\"37\" endIndex=\"50\" /></interactions><output><content><text value=\"[1, 3, 6, 12]\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Certifique-se de escolher <code>print(scores)</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
