            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Ao usar <code>sort()</code> em uma lista de números como <code>scores</code>, os números são ordenados em ordem crescente.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"scores = [\" /><text value=\"3\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"6\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"1\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"12\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\"]\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"scores.sort()\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(scores)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"29\" endIndex=\"30\" /><option startIndex=\"30\" endIndex=\"34\" /><option startIndex=\"34\" endIndex=\"35\" /><option startIndex=\"35\" endIndex=\"36\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"[1, 3, 6, 12]\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Certifique-se de escolher <code>.</code> seguido de <code>sort</code> e depois <code>(</code>, <code>)</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
